locality: Table Mountain above Skeleton Gorge fine white sand between Table Mountain Sandstone rocks.
Riviersondereinde, entrance of Olifantskloof. Vegetation cover ca. 65% (70% of which are Restionaceae); height 80 cm, Protea repens to 2 m) ca. 6 year old vegetation disturbed habitat with pines.
Caledon Wild Flower Garden gentle S-SSE slope. Table Mountain Sandstone burnt.??
